Well...

101
00:09:26,590 --> 00:09:29,730
<i>I kind of went back to his
apartment with him.</i>

102
00:09:29,730 --> 00:09:31,160
His apartment?!

103
00:09:32,270 --> 00:09:34,370
<i>- Apparently he just moved in.</i>
- Idiot!

104
00:09:34,370 --> 00:09:37,540
<i>You shouldn't go home with guys
you don't know.</i>

105
00:09:37,540 --> 00:09:41,199
At first, no-one knows
anyone.

106
00:09:41,199 --> 00:09:45,210
<i>He didn't drag you there did he?
Won't he let you go home?</i>

107
00:09:45,210 --> 00:09:48,020
<i>Don't worry!
I'll be there soon.</i>

108
00:09:48,020 --> 00:09:49,840
What's so funny?

109
00:09:51,020 --> 00:09:53,050
You're a nice person after all.

110
00:09:53,050 --> 00:09:55,600
Aren't you worried at all?

111
00:09:55,600 --> 00:09:58,230
Why am I getting all worked up
over this?

112
00:09:58,230 --> 00:10:02,330
Just give him the phone.
I'll let him have it.

113
00:10:04,100 --> 00:10:06,200
He's in the shower.

114
00:10:07,540 --> 00:10:09,947
What are you thinking?

115
00:10:09,947 --> 00:10:11,500
<i>You're gonna get raped.</i>

116
00:10:11,500 --> 00:10:13,340
Get out of there.

117
00:10:13,340 --> 00:10:16,340
<i>- Did you know about me?</i>
- What?

118
00:10:16,340 --> 00:10:19,350
<i>If I hadn't approached
you at school,</i>

119
00:10:19,350 --> 00:10:21,280
<i>would you have known
who I was?</i>

120
00:10:21,280 --> 00:10:22,800
What are you talking about?

121
00:10:22,800 --> 00:10:28,078
<i>Even if you had seen me around,
you didn't know my name, right?</i>

122
00:10:28,078 --> 00:10:30,260
I'm not the type that
stands out.

123
00:10:30,260 --> 00:10:31,882
<i>What's your point?</i>

124
00:10:34,330 --> 00:10:36,030
<i>Hello?</i>

125
00:10:37,070 --> 00:10:41,230
<i>Hello? Hello?</i>

126
00:10:42,400 --> 00:10:47,570
You would have forgotten me
after we graduated.

127
00:10:48,180 --> 00:10:50,443
And what's your point?

128
00:10:50,443 --> 00:10:53,260
<i>My grades are about average.</i>

129
00:10:53,260 --> 00:10:57,820
Same with sports...
My family is middle-class.

130
00:10:57,820 --> 00:11:01,120
<i>I don't understand. What does
this have to do with anything?</i>

131
00:11:01,120 --> 00:11:05,360
I'm a plain, boring girl.

132
00:11:06,130 --> 00:11:09,090
You even said I get
on your nerves.

133
00:11:09,500 --> 00:11:11,054
That was...

134
00:11:12,170 --> 00:11:16,960
I don't think I'm ever going
to change.

135
00:11:18,970 --> 00:11:20,797
- Goodnight.
<i>- Wait a second!</i>

136
00:11:20,797 --> 00:11:23,200
See you at school.

137
00:11:41,830 --> 00:11:44,454
<i>Principia.</i>

138
00:11:50,100 --> 00:11:54,360
It's freezing!
The shower is broken.

139
00:11:57,010 --> 00:11:58,570
You'll catch a cold.

140
00:11:59,410 --> 00:12:01,650
I can't afford to catch a cold.

141
00:12:08,720 --> 00:12:10,420
Sorry!

142
00:12:12,060 --> 00:12:17,230
Um... I think... well...

143
00:12:26,710 --> 00:12:30,880
You might be angry after we're
come this far, but...

144
00:12:31,400 --> 00:12:33,800
You just broke up with
your boyfriend?

145
00:12:33,800 --> 00:12:35,020
What?

146
00:12:35,020 --> 00:12:39,320
Basically, you became a bit
desperate, but you can't forget

147
00:12:39,320 --> 00:12:43,450
your ex-boyfriend or something.

148
00:12:45,000 --> 00:12:46,390
Am I wrong?

149
00:12:46,390 --> 00:12:51,260
- No. You're pretty close.
- I see.

150
00:12:53,670 --> 00:12:55,366
I'm really sorry.

151
00:12:55,366 --> 00:12:58,000
Not a problem.

152
00:12:59,170 --> 00:13:03,380
Maybe I'm better off this way.

153
00:13:08,420 --> 00:13:14,359
So you lost a loved one?
Or quit your job and then...

154
00:13:14,359 --> 00:13:17,329
- ...I got desperate?
- Yeah.

155
00:13:17,329 --> 00:13:18,815
Something like that.

156
00:13:20,130 --> 00:13:22,090
I guess we're in the same boat.

157
00:13:23,200 --> 00:13:26,830
We shouldn't be throwing
ourselves at each other.

158
00:13:30,640 --> 00:13:32,130
That's right.

159
00:13:33,340 --> 00:13:35,510
But somehow we ended up here.

160
00:13:38,110 --> 00:13:42,110
Yeah. But sometimes things
turn out that way.

161
00:13:44,200 --> 00:13:48,020
In life, you have to put up
with a lot stress.

162
00:13:52,930 --> 00:13:54,630
- Going home?
- Yeah.

163
00:13:54,630 --> 00:13:56,800
- I'll take you.
- I'll be fine.

164
00:13:56,800 --> 00:13:59,200
Then I'll give you money
for the taxi.

165
00:13:59,200 --> 00:14:00,900
I have money. Don't worry.

166
00:14:01,340 --> 00:14:02,800
Okay, then.

167
00:14:07,280 --> 00:14:10,340
This is kind of strange,
isn't it?

168
00:14:12,580 --> 00:14:16,480
Yeah. I wonder why.

169
00:14:30,700 --> 00:14:37,940
If you don't mind,
why not spend the night?

170
00:14:39,770 --> 00:14:41,040
But...

171
00:14:41,040 --> 00:14:42,710
Just to sleep.

172
00:14:43,810 --> 00:14:45,640
I won't do anything.

173
00:14:46,350 --> 00:14:50,920
You can tie my hands
together.

174
00:14:54,160 --> 00:14:56,820
Can't you just sleep beside
me tonight?

175
00:14:57,730 --> 00:14:59,800
It's my one wish in my
whole life.

176
00:15:00,730 --> 00:15:02,520
Your whole life?

177
00:15:04,970 --> 00:15:07,260
I'm going to die soon.

178
00:15:11,670 --> 00:15:13,463
Not really.

179
00:15:47,410 --> 00:15:48,970
I'll stay.

180
00:16:41,300 --> 00:16:46,200
<i>Haru no komorebi no
naka de</i>

181
00:16:46,200 --> 00:16:51,400
<i>Kimi no yasashisa ni</i>

182
00:16:51,400 --> 00:16:53,710
- Good morning!
- Is that all you have to say?

183
00:16:53,710 --> 00:16:55,800
Sorry for hanging up
on you last night.

184
00:16:55,800 --> 00:16:58,200
I got worked up about it
and I couldn't sleep.

185
00:16:58,200 --> 00:16:59,600
Sorry to have worried you.

186
00:16:59,600 --> 00:17:02,400
I just don't want to be held
responsible if something

187
00:17:02,400 --> 00:17:03,800
- happens to you.
- Like what?

188
00:17:03,800 --> 00:17:06,800
Recently there have been some
horrible crimes going on.

189
00:17:06,800 --> 00:17:08,700
You're more serious
than I thought.

190
00:17:08,700 --> 00:17:10,400
- That's enough!
- Sorry.

191
00:17:10,400 --> 00:17:13,120
Whatever. So...?

192
00:17:14,400 --> 00:17:17,150
You went home after
I called, right?

193
00:17:39,750 --> 00:17:42,650
You're not normal, Hina.

194
00:17:42,650 --> 00:17:44,050
Really?

195
00:17:44,050 --> 00:17:46,490
What's with the smile?
You're weird.

196
00:17:46,490 --> 00:17:48,930
I always wanted someone
to tell me

197
00:17:48,930 --> 00:17:50,630
that I'm weird, or different.

198
00:17:50,630 --> 00:17:52,090
- Really?
- Yeah.

199
00:17:52,870 --> 00:17:55,170
So you left in the morning?

200
00:17:55,170 --> 00:17:56,670
Yeah.

201
00:17:56,670 --> 00:17:58,100
What about your parents?

202
00:17:58,100 --> 00:18:01,000
I told them that I was studying
at a best friend's house.

203
00:18:01,000 --> 00:18:03,900
I've never been caught before,
so they didn't question me.

204
00:18:03,900 --> 00:18:06,600
- Best friend?
- Yeah.

205
00:18:08,900 --> 00:18:12,990
And you casually spent
the night with some guy.

206
00:18:13,650 --> 00:18:16,200
He didn't seem like
a bad guy.

207
00:18:16,200 --> 00:18:18,100
You can't tell by looking
at a person.

208
00:18:18,100 --> 00:18:19,100
Yes, you can.

209
00:18:19,100 --> 00:18:21,660
Not by their looks,
but just somehow I knew.

210
00:18:21,660 --> 00:18:23,260
You were the same way.

211
00:18:23,260 --> 00:18:26,500
- Me, too?
- Yeah.

212
00:18:27,100 --> 00:18:29,300
People were spreading
rumors about you,

213
00:18:29,300 --> 00:18:31,530
but I thought they
were wrong.

214
00:18:33,260 --> 00:18:36,000
Exactly who was spreading
rumors?

215
00:18:37,780 --> 00:18:41,070
I can probably guess anyway.

216
00:18:42,220 --> 00:18:43,780
And?

217
00:18:44,320 --> 00:18:47,700
Since you spent the night,
it's pretty obvious.

218
00:18:47,700 --> 00:18:49,450
But I'll ask anyway...

219
00:18:50,060 --> 00:18:53,050
You slept with him, right?

220
00:18:54,760 --> 00:18:57,900
- That's a secret.
- What?

221
00:19:00,230 --> 00:19:02,130
Not that I care.

222
00:19:08,400 --> 00:19:10,040
What are they doing?

223
00:19:10,040 --> 00:19:12,600
There's a new math teacher.

224
00:19:12,600 --> 00:19:15,300
Remember, Shimamura<i>-san</i>
is off on maternity leave.

225
00:19:15,300 --> 00:19:16,300
So?

226
00:19:16,300 --> 00:19:19,100
Just like before, they're putting up
a math problem

227
00:19:19,100 --> 00:19:21,600
that even university professors
can't solve.

228
00:19:24,430 --> 00:19:25,710
That's bullying.

229
00:19:39,240 --> 00:19:42,240
A classic Hamilton-Jacobi
equation.

230
00:19:42,240 --> 00:19:46,040
First, <i>K</i> = <i>C</i>2.

231
00:19:47,650 --> 00:19:51,410
<i>S</i> = integral.

232
00:19:57,000 --> 00:19:58,800
Is he right?

233
00:20:09,370 --> 00:20:11,660
- Let us begin.
- Stand.

234
00:20:12,900 --> 00:20:14,500
Bow.

235
00:20:15,000 --> 00:20:16,600
Sit.

236
00:20:19,300 --> 00:20:20,900
What is it?

237
00:20:22,700 --> 00:20:24,200
Do you have a question?

238
00:20:24,200 --> 00:20:25,850
What are you doing?

239
00:20:28,260 --> 00:20:30,900
I'm Koga. I'll be taking over
Grade 11 math

240
00:20:30,900 --> 00:20:33,510
where Shimamura<i>-sensei</i>
left off.

241
00:20:33,510 --> 00:20:37,770
- What page are we on?
- Page 106.

242
00:20:37,770 --> 00:20:40,100
Everyone, open your books.

243
00:20:45,700 --> 00:20:47,900
I'm head teacher of Grade 11,
Fujimura.

244
00:20:47,900 --> 00:20:49,300
Nice to meet you.

245
00:20:50,080 --> 00:20:56,700
Have you met the principal
and the head teacher?

246
00:20:56,700 --> 00:20:59,580
Oh, I see. Good to hear.

247
00:21:00,250 --> 00:21:03,800
The teachers will finish classes soon,
so I'll introduce you to them.

248
00:21:03,800 --> 00:21:06,900
Oh, here is Tejima Emi<i>-sensei.</i>
She teaches the classics.

249
00:21:06,900 --> 00:21:08,700
She just started last spring.

250
00:21:09,600 --> 00:21:13,000
With her good looks, she seems
wasted on the teaching profession.

251
00:21:13,000 --> 00:21:15,600
Wait. That could be counted
as sexual harassment.

252
00:21:15,600 --> 00:21:18,100
Stop teasing me, boss!

253
00:21:18,100 --> 00:21:20,010
My name is Tejima.
Nice to meet you.

254
00:21:20,010 --> 00:21:22,390
I'm Koga. Nice to be working
with you.

255
00:21:22,390 --> 00:21:25,500
Here is the Japanese history teacher,
Miyada Kôji<i>-sensei.</i>

256
